rComments: She's such a great and enthusiastic professor! She makes classes super digestible. Readings are reasonable, and work is distributed really well throughout the class. If you keep up with readings and listen to her carefully you'll for sure do well :)

Dr. Ford is an amazing lecturer and is very organized and engaging. Grading criteria were very vague, and having 5 quizzes, 2 exams, 2 essays, and a group presentation for this class was a lot of work (especially since the section offered last semester was only exam-based). She is a great prof but gives a heavy workload.
